{"hash":"d523de94b530e00ff7be7c35e8dd330e162f9a17","data":{"post":{"id":"904","title":"Cumulus tool for Substrate and GRANDPA in-depth &#8211; 04. [Sofia Polkadot]","date":"2019-04-01T12:34:01","content":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"678\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004-1024x678.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-915\" srcset=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004-1024x678.jpg 1024w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004-300x199.jpg 300w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004-768x509.jpg 768w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004-870x576.jpg 870w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Polkadot Sofia Meetup 4 &#8211; Cumulus, Substrate and Grandpa</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The time has come for our fourth <a href=\"https://meetup.com/sofia-polkadot\">Polkadot Sofia Meetup</a>. This time the meetup took place in a new cozy venue &#8211; <a href=\"https://www.networking.space/\">Networking Premium Coworking</a>, and hopefully the recording will be better.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We looked over Cumulus &#8211; a tool set for easier development of <g class=\"gr_ gr_4 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_run_anim ContextualSpelling ins-del multiReplace\" id=\"4\" data-gr-id=\"4\">parachains</g> with Substrate.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>It&#8217;s easy to write blockchains using Substrate, and the overhead of writing parachains&#8217; distribution, p2p, database, and synchronization layers is generally high and should be reusable. This project aims to make it easy to write parachains for Polkadot by leveraging the power of Substrate.</p><cite>cumulus github</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>In order for us to understand what cumulus actually is about we needed to dive deep into Substrate and Polkadot. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So we looked over what Substrate framework is build for and what are its main features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Polkadot&#8217;s GRANDPA consensus is a very interesting and quite adaptive algorithm. Milen had prepared a presentation about it, explaining its roots.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"862\" height=\"349\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/grandpa.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-916\" srcset=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/grandpa.png 862w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/grandpa-300x121.png 300w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/grandpa-768x311.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 862px) 100vw, 862px\" /><figcaption>GRANDPA Protocol &#8211; [source: <a href=\"https://github.com/w3f/consensus/blob/master/pdf/grandpa.pdf\">https://github.com/w3f/consensus/blob/master/pdf/grandpa.pdf]</a><br></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see the whole video from the meetup here:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube aligncenter wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/CPgT1PazWz8?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Resources</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1akXdZmnAntq0JDNSmrIirTtUB44xE0-Gu7kJusW-YRs/edit?usp=sharing\">Presentation</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/paritytech/cumulus\">Cumulus</a></li><li><a href=\"https://substrate.readme.io\">Substrate</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot\">Polkadot</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/w3f/consensus/blob/master/pdf/grandpa.pdf\">Grandpa</a></li></ul>\n","excerpt":"<p>The time has come for our fourth Polkadot Sofia Meetup. This time the meetup took place in a new cozy [&hellip;]</p>\n","link":"https://hack.bg/blog/meetups/cumulus-tool-for-substrate-and-grandpa-in-depth-04-sofia-polkadot/","modified":"2019-08-14T21:24:38","featuredMedia":{"sourceUrl":"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/DSC_0004.jpg","altText":"sofia-polkadot-4","mimeType":"image/jpeg","mediaDetails":{"width":4928,"height":3264}},"categories":[{"id":"71","title":"Meet-ups","path":"/category/meetups/","count":22},{"id":"5","title":"Events","path":"/category/events/","count":27}],"tags":[{"id":"95","title":"Cumulus","path":"/tag/cumulus/","count":1},{"id":"96","title":"GRANDPA","path":"/tag/grandpa/","count":1},{"id":"44","title":"Polkadot","path":"/tag/polkadot/","count":4},{"id":"78","title":"Substrate","path":"/tag/substrate/","count":3}],"author":{"name":"Milen","path":"/author/milen/"},"metadata":{"postAudioId":["92f2a40b52e91750a6c44a102a7bc507e55c8595"],"mediumPost":["O:11:\"Medium_Post\":11:{s:16:\"author_image_url\";s:75:\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/fit/c/400/400/1*uTloDoy725Hwdw-PyJg0Yw.jpeg\";s:10:\"author_url\";s:26:\"https://medium.com/@radkov\";s:11:\"byline_name\";N;s:12:\"byline_email\";N;s:10:\"cross_link\";s:3:\"yes\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"3ef07d11a1e9\";s:21:\"follower_notification\";s:3:\"yes\";s:7:\"license\";s:19:\"all-rights-reserved\";s:14:\"publication_id\";s:12:\"6c324f156ae9\";s:6:\"status\";s:5:\"draft\";s:3:\"url\";s:39:\"https://medium.com/@radkov/3ef07d11a1e9\";}"],"postViewsCount":["1511"],"rankMathFocusKeyword":["polkadot,Sofia,cumulus tool"],"rankMathTitle":["Cumulus tool for Substrate and GRANDPA - [Sofia Polkadot]"],"rankMathDescription":[]}}},"context":{}}